      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 345: Saving the published address requires both `publishedAddress` and `publishedPort` to be valid every time either field disappears. If an existing SIP account has one of these values empty, editing the other field first will reset the user\u0027s input and make the setting effectively impossible to configure one field at a time. Save the field independently, or allow the edit screen to validate/save only the value being edited. For example, split this into `savePublishedAddress()` and `savePublishedPort()` and wire each row to its corresponding save action.",
      "revId": "5740829be273431250d19cb83f2f2179f1788462",
