      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 363: `isValidStunServer` treats the first colon as the host/port separator, so valid IPv6 STUN server addresses such as `[2001:db8::1]:3478` or `2001:db8::1` are rejected. SIP connectivity settings should not block IPv6 endpoints. Parse bracketed IPv6 host:port explicitly, or use URLComponents/NWEndpoint-style parsing that supports hostnames, IPv4, and IPv6 literals.",
      "revId": "5740829be273431250d19cb83f2f2179f1788462",
